  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance to asylum seekers and refugees from South Sudan (ACT Appeal ETH 141)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Construct latrines, showers, and hand washing basins;  

2. Provide behavioral change training to community leaders and other influential members, related to latrine usage;  

3. Conduct community mobilization and awareness events;  

4. Provide Community Based Psycho Social workshops to selected target community;  

5. Construct a semi-permanent entertainment hall, equip it with sport equipment, and train center&apos;s facilitators;  

6. Develop and equip child and youth friendly spaces;  

7. Construct and equip a secondary and vocational education school and hire the needed staff.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South Sudan refugees, camp personnel, community leaders and members</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objectives of the project are: 1.&#xA0;Hygiene and sanitation -  Sustained and expanded use of sanitation services ensured for the target communities; 2.&#xA0;Psychosocial support &#x2013; Psychosocial support wellbeing of the most affected refugees (rape victims, Gender Base Violence, unaccompanied children, pregnant women, elderly etc.) improved; and 3. Secondary Education and Vocational Training &#x2013; Refugees become middle level workers after completion of secondary education or are enabled to join higher education.  The project will also enhance the self-reliance and employability of refugees through access to education and vocational training.</narrative>
  </description>
